_:Nc5398cba9d7746b3b2e65c21a45aed36 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Louise Haigh was the Secretary of State for Transport from 5 July 2024 to 29 November 2024.</p>\n\n<p>She was the youngest female Cabinet Minister to ever be appointed.  </p>\n\n<p>Louise was elected as the <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr> for Sheffield Heeley in May 2015.  </p>\n\n<p>Since being elected as an <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr>, Louise has held a number of shadow ministerial roles, including Shadow Secretary of State for Transport from 2021 to 2024.  </p>\n\n<p>Louise served as a Special Constable in the Met Police between 2009 and 2011 and worked for Aviva as a public policy manager from 2012 to 2015. </p>\n\n<p>Louise studied politics at Nottingham University and law at Birkbeck, University of London.</p>\n\n" .
_:N390fea74ebe94bf28390cfeda3648ca6 <http://schema.org/itemListElement> _:N9c88667baf2242ad9828775eb38b1ef3 .
